<DOC><DOCNO> AP900203-0027 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-03-90 0310EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-People-Barr     02-03 0169</FIRST><SECOND>PM-People-Barr,0174</SECOND><HEAD>Entertainer Roseanne Barr Reports Love Letters Stolen</HEAD><DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Love letters written by actressRoseanne Barr to Tom Arnold, her newlywed husband, have been stolenand are being offered for sale to various periodicals, a publicistsaid.   ``Our purpose in sending the (announcement) out is to notifypeople that these letters are stolen,'' publicist Alana Rothsteinsaid Friday.   ``We're saying, `yes it is for real, and yes they are stolen,and if somebody decides to publish them, then down the road they'llhave to deal with the repercussions.'''   Barr's public relations firm had received inquiries from severalpublishers who had been contacted by someone who was offering tosell the letters.   Rothstein said she didn't know how exactly how many letters werestolen, or when. She said at least several letters were stolensometime within the last three weeks.   Asked if the theft had been reported to police, Rothstein saidit was a legal matter and was being handled by Miss Barr'sattorneys.</TEXT></DOC>